<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 1:56AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE FOG POSSIBLE EARLY THIS MORNING...
Patchy dense fog is expected across portions of Connecticut
early this morning. Visibilities may be reduced to a quarter mile
or less at times. With temperatures near freezing, its possible a
few few slick spots may develop on roads and sidewalks.
Motorists should exercise caution by reducing speed, leaving
extra space between vehicles, and using low-beam headlights in
areas of low visibility.</description>
